The paper deals with an algorithmic problem in the area of online matching, which is a subfield of algorithmic game theory and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are all likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of online primal dual algorithms, which are a common tool in optimization and information theory, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a simplified version of an existing algorithm, which could be of interest to researchers in the area of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
